    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear you on it being complicated, but i feel like i'm getting a lot of \"on the one hand, on the other hand\" answers. as a business consultant, can you just give me a straight answer? if a state legislature pushes a high wage increase in a low-cost area, is it more likely that the local economy thrives from the extra cash in pockets, or that small businesses just end up folding under the cost? which one is the more realistic risk for someone in my position?",
